div.p:
But seeing you are pleased to say further, That if you called me a Liar; though such a Proposition sounded like an Affirmative, yet it was no Affirmative Proposition, but finally resolved into a Negative, and can no otherwise be proved than as a Negative may. I demonstrate the contrary thus. You know that Mentiri, is derived from Contra mentem ire, and therefore you will excuse the Latin;


Omnis qui it contra mentem, mentitur;

At Doctor Monro it contra mentem:

Ergo.
